AGI - A strong earthquake struck the Basilicata, in particular the area around Potenza. The magnitude recorded by INGV is 4.2 but the sisma has also been heard in Matera and, as is noted by the comments on social media, in different regions of Centro-Sud.
<div </div
According to the data of the Ingv the shock occurred six kilometers from the Municipality of Vaglio Basilicata (Potenza) to a depth of 14,3 kilometers. The Civil Protection Operating Room is activated in Potenza. At the moment there is no damage. Several schools, in Potenza, were issued by precautionary institutions. &nbsp;
<h2>Customs closed in town
The Municipal Operating Centre of Potenza has been activated with the Civil Protection Operating Room contactable at 0971-415832 and 366-9394022. "The order for the suspension of teaching activities in all schools of every order and degree, for today's day," says the mayor of Potenza, Vincenzo Telesca.
<h2>Bardi, no significant damage
"Immediately immediately after the shock of this morning (Magnitudo 4.2), registered in the province of Potenza, with an epicenter about 6 km west of Vaglio and distinctly warned by the population, the Regional Civil Protection was activated". This is what the president of the Basilicata Region, Vito Bardi knows.
"Number of reports received by citizens but at the moment, there is no significant damage. We continue to monitor the situation - Bardi concludes - to verify possible criticalities and ensure the safety of the Lucans". &nbsp;
